items.sentence: I suspect that Tom and Mary have gone to Australia.
I suspect Tom and Mary have already left Australia.
Did you know Tom used to teach French in Australia?
I wish that we could go to Australia and visit Tom.
I wish Tom would stay in Australia until Christmas.
I told Tom that I'd stay in Australia until Monday.
I thought that Tom would be in Australia on Monday.
I thought that Tom would be returning to Australia.
I thought that Tom would go to Australia with Mary.
I sure hope that Tom comes to Australia in October.
